JOHANNESBURG – Celebrities have come out batting in support of hip-hop star Cassper Nyovest’s #FillUpFNBStadium concert. The ambitious rapper is planning to entertain about 75,000 fans at the 90,000 plus capacity stadium in the south of Johannesburg on December 2. Internationally acclaimed DJ Black Coffee said he will be spending R20,000 on Nyovest‘s #FillUpFNBStadium tickets for fans every Friday until the show. On Saturday fellow rapper Riky Rick announced that he had purchased tickets for the show amounting to R20,000. Police Minister Fikile Mbalula has pledged to buy 10 tickets for the event. Personalities like Bob Mabena, Kwesta, Da L.E.S, Brian Temba‏, Gigi Lamayne, Major League DJs, Nadia Nakai, Moozlie, Kuli Roberts, Khanyi Mbau, Pearl Thusi, Rami Chuene, Thando Thabethe and Rob Forbes have all come out in support of the rapper. The Doc Shebeleza hitmaker has already had successful concerts with #FillUpTheDome and #FillUpOrlandoStadium in 2015 and 2016 respectively. eNCA